@realmoney Reducing WalMart Ahead of Earnings For three weeks I have been buying $WMT on every dip. However, reflecting a less attractive reward to risk I am now selling down my WalMart from very large sized to medium sized - ahead of the company's EPS report tomorrow.

I placed WMT on my Best Ideas List only three weeks ago at $137/share. The shares have hit a 52 week high this morning and are trading at almost $153/share. Upside/downside is a dynamic concept and the +12% gain in less than a month has produced a less compelling ratio of reward
